<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-28-0926 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Rancho Seco nuclear power plant, near Sacramento, California has beenclosed 13 of its first 18 months in operation due to malfunctioning equipment.Today, the plant is shut down again, this time as a result of its thirdserious cooling accident. Between 1975 and 1986, average rates have increasedby 184%. Given the safety and economic history of the plant, a groupcalled Sacramentans for Safe Energy (SAFE) recently lead a successfulpetition drive that will put the issue on the ballot. The election willbe held in June, 1988.</TEXT></DOC>